  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Promoting Freedom of Expression and Safety of Journalists in Ethiopia</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Ethiopia has shown significant progress in freedom of expression and press freedom since 2018 with the government taking important measures including releasing of journalists from prison, unblocking of websites and blogs, allowing of diaspora media to operate in the country and initiating institutional and legal reforms. The current state FoE, however, is critical both in fostering and sustaining the freedoms and avoiding potential backtracks against the development already achieved. The safety and security risks of journalists is also from other powerful groups. The self-regulation and professionalism is in its early stages and journalists associations need to be strengthened to contribute to strengthening FoE in Ethiopia.</narrative>
  </description>
